# Subsea Kill Sheet — Flutter

A single-file Flutter implementation of the **IWCF Subsea BOP Vertical Well Kill Sheet** (API Field Units), combining an interactive mobile screen and a pixel-accurate A4 PDF export in one self-contained Dart file.

---

## What it does

- Provides a full **kill-sheet entry form** split into 8 collapsible sections
- **Calculates live** as you type — KMW, ICP, FCP, CLF, InitDyn CP, MAASP, volumes, strokes, times
- Exports a properly formatted **IWCF A4 PDF** (2 pages) via share sheet
- Saves and restores up to **5 named slots** stored as JSON on-device
- Renders a **live Subsea well diagram** (marine riser, choke line, casing shoe, open hole, BOP) that updates as you type

---

## Sections

| # | Section | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Formation Strength Data | FST, Mud Weight at Test, Max Allowable MW (C), Initial MAASP |
| 2 | Current Well Data | Marine riser, choke line, mud density, casing shoe, hole data — with a live subsea well diagram |
| 3 | Pump Data | Pump displacement, SPM, slow-pump Riser/Choke pressure loss, auto-calculated CLF |
| 4 | Volumetric Data & Pump Strokes | Drill string, open hole annulus, casing annulus, choke line, active surface, marine riser × DP |
| 5 | Kick Data & Kill Mud Weight | SIDPP, SICP, Pit Gain, KMW formula |
| 6 | Circulating Pressures | ICP, FCP, L (ICP−FCP), L/100 strokes |
| 7 | Initial Dynamic Casing Pressure | IntDyn CP at Kill Pump Rate = SICP − CLF |
| 8 | Step-Down Chart | Auto-generated pressure step-down table and graph |

---

## Formulas used
Max Allowable MW (C)       =  MWT + FST / (Shoe TVD × 0.052)           [round down, 1 dp]
Initial MAASP              =  [(C) − Current MW] × Shoe TVD × 0.052    [round down, whole]
Kill Mud Weight (KMW)      =  MW + SIDPP / (Hole TVD × 0.052)          [round up,   1 dp]
Choke Line Friction (CLF)  =  Choke Line Pressure − Riser Pressure
ICP                        =  Riser Dynamic Pressure Loss + SIDPP
FCP                        =  (KMW / Current MW) × Riser DPL
L                          =  ICP − FCP
L / 100 strokes            =  L / DS Total Strokes × 100
InitDyn CP at KPR          =  SICP − CLF
Volume                     =  Length × Capacity
Strokes                    =  Volume / Pump Displacement                [ceiling]
Time (min)                 =  Strokes / SPM                            [ceiling]

---

## Key Subsea differences from Surface sheet

| Parameter | Surface | Subsea |
|---|---|---|
| BOP location | Surface | Seabed |
| Pressure loss term | K (drill-string only) | L (accounts for choke line) |
| Extra lengths | — | Marine Riser, Choke Line |
| Choke Line Friction | Not applicable | CLF = Choke − Riser pressure |
| Initial Dynamic Casing Pressure | Not applicable | IntDyn CP = SICP − CLF |
| Volume sections | DS, OH, Csg annulus | DS, OH, Csg annulus, Choke line, Marine Riser × DP |
| Kill TVD reference | Hole TVD | Hole TVD (KMW), Shoe TVD (MAASP) |

