## File structure

Everything lives in **`subsea_kill_sheet_screen.dart`**:
SubseaKillSheetPdfData         — immutable data model passed to the PDF builder
PDF constants / fonts          — colours, border weights, Helvetica variants
PDF builder functions          — header, formation, pump data, right panel/diagram,
volume table, kill-sheet page 2 with step-down graph
_generateSubseaKillSheetPdf()  — assembles the 2-page A4 PDF, returns Uint8List
SubseaKillSheetScreen          — StatefulWidget entry point
_SubseaKillSheetScreenState    — all state, controllers, calcs, save/load, UI
_SubseaWellDiagramPainter      — CustomPainter for the live subsea well schematic
_StepDownChartPainter          — CustomPainter for the step-down graph
_SubseaInlineDatePicker        — overlay calendar dropdown
_SubseaSlotPickerDialog        — 5-slot save/open selector dialog
_SubseaSlotLabelDialog         — name-entry dialog for save slots

---

## Usage
```dart
Navigator.push(
  context,
  MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => const SubseaKillSheetScreen()),
);
```

No constructor arguments needed — all state is managed internally.

---

## Notes

- Built for **personal learning** based on IWCF kill-sheet methodology.
- Not intended for official, certified, or commercial well-control use.
- PDF layout targets **A4 portrait** at standard margins.
- All calculations follow **API field units** (ppg, psi, feet, barrels, bbl/ft).
- The subsea diagram painter draws five colour-coded depth lines: Red = Marine Riser, Blue = Hole TVD, Orange = Casing Shoe TVD, Green = Open Hole, Violet = Choke Line.

